<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/50076988-laurelle"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1450042131i/50076988._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/50076988-laurelle">Laurelle</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">From my perspective as a person trying to make writing part of my daily life, I&apos;d say Bird by Bird is more of a pep talk/psychotherapy session for wri<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">From my perspective as a person trying to make writing part of my daily life, I'd say Bird by Bird is more of a pep talk/psychotherapy session for writers. Sitting home alone writing can be more than a little crazy-making, so it's nice to have some reassurance that the craziness is normal, along with some tools for getting to the next day.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
