<div id="review_307188608" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/307188608" />
    <a title="Perry" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6354112-perry"><img alt="Perry" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1626605254p2/6354112.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/307188608?book_show_action=true">Apr 05, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Perry" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Perry" href="/user/show/6354112-perry">Perry</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6354112-perry?shelf=tools-of-trade">tools-of-trade</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6354112-perry?shelf=scrittura">scrittura</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer307188608" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6176371261966913308"><b>Swell Songs Sung So Well</b><br/><br/>This little book sings so sweetly. You&apos;ve probably read in other books some version of the optimism, pointers and warnings that are covered here. Yet, you&apos;ve probably not read one as practical or as well-written as this. <br/><br/>Anne Lamott&apos;s book is a virtuosic &quot;Best of&quot; LP, for writers and other creative artists, from which one may choose among many tracks of anecdotes, experience and hope. It&apos;s something you can pull out from time to time to put you on the right track, get you</span>
  <span id="freeText6176371261966913308" style="display:none"><b>Swell Songs Sung So Well</b><br /><br />This little book sings so sweetly. You've probably read in other books some version of the optimism, pointers and warnings that are covered here. Yet, you've probably not read one as practical or as well-written as this. <br /><br />Anne Lamott's book is a virtuosic "Best of" LP, for writers and other creative artists, from which one may choose among many tracks of anecdotes, experience and hope. It's something you can pull out from time to time to put you on the right track, get you unstuck and, in all cases, on to conjuring magic from your imagination onto the blank screen or sheet of paper sitting in front of you.<br /><br />I highly recommend this book.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="6176371261966913308" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
